name: Bungisngis
description: Bungisngis are one-eyed forest giants. They are the Filipino counterpart of the Greek Cyclops. Standing over ten feet tall, these creatures possess immense strength - more than enough to overpower a Carabao. Bungisngis are constantly laughing and enjoy bullying forest animals to steal their food. They are, however, extremely dimwitted and can easily be tricked.
